com.basho.riak.client.api.convert

Class Converter<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.basho.riak.client.api.convert.Converter<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type to convert to
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    JSONConverter, PassThroughConverter, StringConverter

    public abstract class Converter<T>
extends Object
    The Converter acts as a bridge between the core and the user level API, specifically for ORM.

    Subclasses will override the fromDomain(java.lang.Object) and fromDomain(java.lang.Object) methods to convert the value portion of a RiakObject to a domain object.

    Since:
    2.0
    Author:
    Brian Roach

      • toDomain

        public abstract T toDomain(BinaryValue value,
                           String contentType)
                    throws ConversionException
        Convert the value portion of a RiakObject to a domain object.

        Implementations override this method to convert the value contained in a RiakObject to an instance of a domain object.

        Parameters:
        value - the value portion of a RiakObject to convert to a domain object
        contentType - The content type of the RiakObject
        Returns:
        a new instance of the domain object
        Throws:
        ConversionException

      • fromDomain

        public Converter.OrmExtracted fromDomain(T domainObject,
                                         Namespace namespace,
                                         BinaryValue key)
        Convert from a domain object to a RiakObject.

        The domain object itself may be completely annotated with everything required to produce a RiakObject except for the value portion. This will prefer annotated items over the Location passed in.

        Parameters:
        domainObject - a domain object to be stored in Riak.
        namespace - the namespace in Riak
        key - the key for the object
        Returns:
        data to be stored in Riak.
